sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159215
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Membrane-anchored SpyTag with secretory SpyCatcher_nLuc reporter fusion translational unit
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part encodes a translational unit consisting two fusion proteins, a Membrane-anchored SpyTag and a secretory SpyCatcher_nLuc (IgKappa-SigP_SpyCatcher_nLuc) reporter fusion to show if post-translational protein fusion like reaction happens between the membrane-localized tag protein and the secretory fusion protein containing N-terminal SpyCatcher and C-terminal NanoLuc Luciferase. As a translational unit both fusion proteins are seperated by a polioviral IRES to allow bicistronic expression in eukaryotic systems. To express this system you only have to insert your favored promoter/terminator in the prefix/suffix of this part. For further information, please see under the subparts linked in the text.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159300
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Polioviral Internal Ribosome Entry Site (IRES) for polycistronic expression in eukaryotes
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains the Internal Ribosome Entry Site (IRES) of the human poliovirus 1 Mahoney strain which allows polycistronic expression systems in eukaryotic systems. This part is flanked by RFC[10] pre- and suffix. By cloning this part betweens CDSs, many proteins/peptides can expressed by a single promoter and terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159995
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 10/25 N-Part Assembly Scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Assembly scar between RFC[10] coding/non-coding Biobrick and RFC[25] N-part Biobrick (not RFC[25] standard prefix!). Formally it has the same scar like the assembly scar between RFC[10] coding/non-coding Biobrick and RFC[10] coding Biobrick.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: TU Munich 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159996
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 25/10 NC Assembly Scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Assembly scar between RFC[25] Biobrick and RFC[10] non-coding Biobrick.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: TU Munich 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159207
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Membrane-anchored SpyTag in RFC[25] N-Part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for a membrane-anchored version of SpyTag [http://parts.igem.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K1159201 BBa_K1159201] for the chassis ''Physcomitrella patens''. Please see subparts for for further description. This construct is flanked by RFC[25] N-part prefix and suffix. Note: This means only protein fusions to the C-terminus of this part is possible, adding promoters (typically RFC[10]) into the prefix or terminators/IRES (typically RFC[10]) into the suffix of this part is nevertheless possible.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159211
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Secretory SpyCatcher_nLuc fusion (IgKappa-SigP_SpyCatcher_nLuc) in RFC[25] N-Part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Secretory Fusionprotein consisting N-terminal SpyCatcher and C-terminal nLuc (IgKappa-SigP_SpyCatcher_nLuc) in RFC[25] N-Part. This construct is flanked by RFC[25] N-part prefix and suffix. Note: This means only protein fusions to the C-terminus of this part is possible, adding promoters (typically RFC[10]) into the prefix or terminators/IRES (typically RFC[10]) into the suffix of this part is nevertheless possible.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: NanoLuc Luciferase in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: x
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: TU Munich 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159993
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 25/25 Assembly Scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Assembly scar between RFC[25] Biobrick and RFC[25] Biobrick.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: TU Munich 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159316
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: SERK-Receptor TMD with C-terminal GFP and N-terminal Strep-tag II TEV-site linker in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part codes for the Transmembrane Domain of SERK Receptor from ''Physcomitrella patens'' with a C-terminal (intracellular) GFPmut1 fusion and a N-terminal fusion to a linker containing ''Strep''-tag II and a TEV cleavage site; SERK TMD and GFPmut1 are seperated by a middle long linker. This part is flanked by RFC[25] pre- and suffix for further protein fusions.
Note: A signal peptide is needed for membrane integration.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: TU Munich 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159202
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Secretory SpyCatcher (IgKappa-SigP_SpyCatcher) in RFC[25] N-Part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part encodes the SpyCatcher [http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K1159200 BBa_K1159200] with a N-terminal signal peptide for secretion (Ig Kappa signal peptide from ''Mus musculus'') which also works in moss ''Physcomitrella patens''. This construct is flanked by RFC[25] N-part prefix and suffix. Note: This means only protein fusions to the C-terminus of this part is possible, adding promoters (typically RFC[10]) into the prefix or terminators/IRES (typically RFC[10]) into the suffix of this part is nevertheless possible.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159205
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Secretory SpyTag (SERK-SigP_SpyTag) in RFC[25] N-Part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part encodes the SpyTag [http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K1159201 BBa_K1159201] with a N-terminal signal peptide for secretion (SERK receptor signal peptide from ''Physcomitrella patens''). This construct is flanked by RFC[25] N-part prefix and suffix. Note: This means only protein fusions to the C-terminus of this part is possible, adding promoters (typically RFC[10]) into the prefix or terminators/IRES (typically RFC[10]) into the suffix of this part is nevertheless possible.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159303
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Signal Peptide of SERK Receptor from Physcomitrella patens in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the signal peptide from the SERK receptor (Somatic Embryogenesis RECEPTOR KINAS) of ''Physocmitrella patens''. The signal peptide induces translocation of the protein into the Endoplasmatic Reticulum (ER) for secretion or membrane integration. Protein fused to the C-terminus of this part should be secreted or otherwise if the part fused region contains a transmembrane domain it will be integrated in cytoplasmatic membrane. This part starts with a consensus sequence for ''Physcomitrella patens'' which allows efficient translation start. Furthermore, this part is flanked by RFC[25] N-part pre- and suffix for fusions to the C-terminus of this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: TU Munich 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159309
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 19 AA Linker with N-terminal Strep-tag II and C-terminal TEV cleavage site in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part encodes a 19 amino acids long linker with a N-terminal ''Strep''-tag II and a C-terminal cleavage site for the TEV Protease. For further protein fusions this part is flanked by RFC[25} pre- and suffix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: TU Munich 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159315
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: TMD of SERK Receptor from Physcomitrella patens with C-terminal GFP fusion in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the Transmembrane Domain of SERK Receptor from <i>Physcomitrella patens'' with a C-terminal (intracellular) GFPmut1 fusion; SERK TMD and GFPmut1 are seperated by a middle long linker. Still, a signal peptide is needed for membrane integration. This part is flanked by RFC[25] pre- and suffix for further protein fusions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: TU Munich 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159304
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Signal Peptide of Ig Kappa chain from Mus musculus in RFC[25] N-part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the signal peptide of the Ig Kappa chain from ''Mus musculus''. The signal peptide induces translocation of the protein into the Endoplasmatic Reticulum (ER) for secretion or membrane integration. Protein fused to the C-terminus of this part should be secreted or otherwise if the part fused region contains a transmembrane domain it will be integrated in cytoplasmatic membrane. This part starts with a consensus sequence for Physcomitrella patens which allows efficient translation start. Furthermore, this part is flanked by RFC[25] N-part pre- and suffix for fusions to the C-terminus of this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: TU Munich 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159200
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Splitted and engineered N-terminal FbaB for isopeptide bound formation (SpyCatcher) in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for a protein that recognizes and forms a covalent isopeptide bound to a oligopeptide. That oligopeptide can be found under BBa_K1159201. This part is flanked by RFC[25] pre- and suffix for further protein fusions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: Reactive Lys for isopeptide forming reaction

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159305
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Transmembrane domain of SERK Receptor from Physcomitrella patens in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is encoding the transmembrane region of the SERK Receptor from ''Physcomitrella patens''. For membrane translocation a N-terminal signal peptide is still necessary for translocation through the ER membrane. This part is flanked by RFC[25] pre- and suffix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: TU Munich 2013

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: Transmembrane Domain of SERK Receptor from ''P. patens''

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159201
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Splitted and engineered C-terminal FbaB for isopeptide bound formation (SpyTag) in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for a oligopeptide that is recognized and bound by a covalent isopeptide bound to a protein, called SpyCatcher. That catcher protein for this oligopeptdie can be found under BBa_K1159200. This part is flanked by RFC[25] pre- and suffix for further protein fusions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: Reactive Asp for isopeptide forming reaction

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: MiddleLink
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Middle Linker ( Gly-Gly-Ser-Gly)x2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Oligos synthesized by sigma. Hybridized by PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a linker, it can be used to connect two parts and add additional space between these parts. That can be necessary to avoid interactions between these parts. We used this part to connect our protein domains with our lipocalin domains, for our project the universal endonuclease.The sequence produced the aminoacids Gly-Gly-Ser-Gly-Gly-Gly-Ser-Gly .
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Freiburg Bioware09
